        "title": "Add doctor upgrade coverage",
        "body": "## Summary\n- add a doctor-repair-upgrade scenario that clones a source env, applies legacy config, upgrades to the target, runs doctor --fix, then checks status/plugins/models/logs\n- add doctor-upgrade profile with five legacy config states across core, plugin, provider, channel, and runtime-pin boundaries\n- write state evidence markers citing recent OpenClaw PRs/issues/commits that explain why each profile detects breaking changes\n- add catalog/selfcheck coverage for the new profile resolving all five obligations\n\n## Verification\n- node bin/kova.mjs plan --json\n- node bin/kova.mjs matrix plan --profile doctor-upgrade --target local-build:/tmp/openclaw --json\n- node bin/kova.mjs run --target local-build:/tmp/openclaw --scenario doctor-repair-upgrade --state legacy-core-config-doctor-2026-4-24 --source-env \"Team Env\" --report-dir /tmp --json\n- git diff --check\n- node --check support/write-doctor-upgrade-state.mjs\n\n## Notes\n- npm run check reaches and passes doctor-upgrade-plan-json, but the full self-check is red in this local environment because OCM is not installed/on PATH and setup/auth prerequisite checks fail before any real scenario execution.\n- npm run test:snapshots is also red here because the committed report fixture artifacts referenced by the snapshot harness are absent locally; plan snapshots additionally reflect local OS/Node version drift.",
